y) profitless, or (specially), an idol","kjv_def":"vain, vanity","pos":"adjective","usage":"vain(5x), vanities(1x)"},"G3123":{"id":"G3123","lemma":"μᾶλλον","translit":"mâllon","derivation":"neuter of the comparative of the same as G3122 (μάλιστα);","strongs_def":"(adverbially) more (in a greater degree)) or rather","kjv_def":"+ better, X far, (the) more (and more), (so) much (the more), rather","pos":"adverb","usage":"more(32x), rather(33x)"},"G3138":{"id":"G3138","lemma":"Μάρκος","translit":"Márkos","derivation":"of Latin origin;","strongs_def":"Marcus, a Christian","kjv_def":"Marcus, Mark","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Mark(5x), Marcus(3x)"},"G3105":{"id":"G3105","lemma":"μαίνομαι","translit":"maínomai","derivation":"middle voice from a primary (to long for;","strongs_def":"through the idea of insensate craving); to rave as a \"maniac\"","kjv_def":"be beside self (mad)","pos":"verb"},"G3167":{"id":"G3167","lemma":"μεγαλεῖος","translit":"megaleîos","derivation":"from G3173 (μέγας);","strongs_def":"magnificent, i.e. (neuter, plural as noun) a conspicuous favor, or (subjectively) perfection","kjv_def":"great things, wonderful works","pos":"adjective"},"G3145":{"id":"G3145","lemma":"μασσάομαι","translit":"massáomai","derivation":"from a primary (to handle or squeeze);","strongs_def":"to chew","kjv_def":"gnaw","pos":"verb","usage":"gnaw(1x)"},"G3140":{"id":"G3140","lemma":"μαρτυρέω","translit":"martyréō","derivation":"from G3144 (μάρτυς);","strongs_def":"to be a witness, i.e. testify (literally or figuratively)","kjv_def":"charge, give (evidence), bear record, have (obtain, of) good (honest) report, be well reported of, testify, give (have) testimony, (be, bear, give, obtain) witness","pos":"verb","usage":"testify(19x), witness(5x)"},"G3130":{"id":"G3130","lemma":"μανία","translit":"manía","derivation":"from G3105 (μαίνομαι);","strongs_def":"craziness","kjv_def":"(+ make) X mad"},"G3198":{"id":"G3198","lemma":"Μελχισεδέκ","translit":"Melchisedék","derivation":